            <section xml:id="group___t_m___l_o_w_p_o_w_e_r___functions_1gaabe385d1398fe280b93db08bd615c966">
                <title>void TM_LOWPOWER_SleepUntilInterrupt (uint8_t delay_timer)</title> <emphasis>Put device into sleep mode.</emphasis>
                
<para><formalpara><title>Note: </title>

<para>MCU will be in sleep mode until next interrupt occured. This means, that delay timer (Systick or any user selectable delay timer) can wakeup STM32F4 too. If you want prevent this, you have to disable delay timer as well it. This can be done with this function.</para>
</formalpara>

                <formalpara>
                    <title/>
